# chord note selection with 3 notes in 4-voice mode: select1/3/5 = root/3rd/5th
# = C,E,G. "If you select three notes, output4 will play the same as output1."
# So the four voices are C,E,G,C. spread=0 -> the doubled C is a unison with O1.
#   O1=C(semi 0), O2=E(4), O3=G(7), O4=C(0, same as O1)
patch <<<
[chord]
    output1 = O1
    output2 = O2
    output3 = O3
    output4 = O4
    select1 = 1
    select3 = 1
    select5 = 1
>>>
@0 expect O1 0 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O2 0.0333333 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O3 0.0583333 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O4 0 tol 1e-5
